data.text: Coalition forces return to Patrol Base Mohammed after a patrol Feb. 24 through Mirabad Valley, Afghanistan. PB Mohammed is the first base in Mirabad Valley, built from scratch solely for Afghan National Security Forces, said Australian Army Maj. Brenton J. Pearce, commander of Combat Team B, 2nd Mentoring Task Force, Combined Team Uruzgan.
